 Angeles or Palm Springs?

50
00:06:20,897 --> 00:06:23,141
- You seem to have all
 the information today.

51
00:06:24,245 --> 00:06:26,075
Why don't you tell me?

52
00:06:29,181 --> 00:06:30,666
- You know something?

53
00:06:30,666 --> 00:06:32,978
I'm sure that that wit got
 you by in Baker and Colgate

54
00:06:32,978 --> 00:06:37,431
and Virginia Law, but it just
 doesn't cut it down here.

55
00:06:38,605 --> 00:06:39,537
You know what I mean?

56
00:06:39,537 --> 00:06:40,607
Let's not go down that path.

57
00:06:42,022 --> 00:06:44,921
And if you're so goddamn smart,
what are you doing in here?

58
00:06:47,855 --> 00:06:52,860
Look, before we get started,
 you want like a soda?

59
00:06:53,343 --> 00:06:54,517
Coffee?

60
00:06:54,517 --> 00:06:56,968
Here, look, have a cigarette.

61
00:06:56,968 --> 00:06:57,969
[pack thuds]

62
00:06:57,969 --> 00:06:58,797
Relax.

63
00:07:00,730 --> 00:07:02,180
[Nick sighs]

64
00:07:02,180 --> 00:07:04,009
- Yeah, that's how I
 used to do it, too.

65
00:07:07,910 --> 00:07:09,429
- Excuse me?

66
00:07:09,429 --> 00:07:11,258
- Look, let's just cut
 the bullshit, okay?

67
00:07:11,258 --> 00:07:13,260
You know who you're talking to.

68
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:16,470
See, the first
 thing I used to do

69
00:07:16,470 --> 00:07:17,989
is get the relationship going,

70
00:07:19,369 --> 00:07:20,854
establish some contact.

71
00:07:21,682 --> 00:07:22,994
Care for a cigarette?

72
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:29,000
[Agent Winslow sighs]

73
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:32,417
[lighter clicks]

74
00:07:32,417 --> 00:07:33,867
[Nick laughs]

75
00:07:33,867 --> 00:07:35,316
Oh, here we go, baby!

76
00:07:35,316 --> 00:07:38,734
[men laughing]
[ball bouncing]

77
00:07:38,734 --> 00:07:41,461
Hehe, got you there! [laughs]

78
00:07:41,461 --> 00:07:43,221
[ball bouncing]

79
00:07:43,221 --> 00:07:44,878
Ho, coming in to me!

80
00:07:45,982 --> 00:07:47,467
[ball bouncing]
[Anson grunting]

81
00:07:47,467 --> 00:07:50,159
[Nick chuckles]

82
00:07:51,712 --> 00:07:52,817
- Nice serve.

83
00:07:54,784 --> 00:07:56,821
So, when were you
 gonna tell me, pal?

84
00:07:56,821 --> 00:07:57,994
- Tell you what?

85
00:07:57,994 --> 00:07:59,651
- That you're getting
 kicked upstairs.

86
00:07:59,651 --> 00:08:00,583
- I'm not going anywhere.

87
00:08:00,583 --> 00:08:01,826
Serve the ball, let's go.

88
00:08:01,826 --> 00:08:03,137
- Deputy Attorney
 General's office

89
00:08:03,137 --> 00:08:05,277
ordered a job eval
 on you, buddy.

90
00:08:05,277 --> 00:08:07,487
I smell justice.

91
00:08:07,487 --> 00:08:12,492
[ball bouncing]
 [floor squeaking]

92
00:08:19,119 --> 00:08:20,430
Yep.

93
00:08:20,430 --> 00:08:21,535
Lousy back hand.

94
00:08:22,847 --> 00:08:24,573
- I'm trying to concentrate
 here, do you mind?

95
00:08:24,573 --> 00:08:25,505
Thank you.

96
00:08:25,505 --> 00:08:26,920
- There's rumblings going around

97
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,680
that Federal's putting together
a new team of hot shots

98
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:30,510
to work in organized crimes.

99
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:31,752
- Who told you that?

100
00:08:31,752 --> 00:08:32,581
- Serve.

101
00:08:34,824 --> 00:08:37,517
[ball bouncing]

102
00:08:40,036 --> 00:08:43,281
I gotta tell ya,
 I'm pretty jealous.

103
00:08:43,281 --> 00:08:45,283
They must want you
 pretty bad, too.

104
00:08:45,283 --> 00:08:48,735
Your background check
 alone was this thick.

105
00:08:53,705 --> 00:08:56,225
- What's the score?
 - Nine all.

106
00:08:57,571 --> 00:08:59,504
[ball bouncing]

107
00:08:59,504 --> 00:09:00,919
[Anson shouts]

108
00:09:00,919 --> 00:09:05,475
My serve. [laughs]

109
00:09:07,823 --> 00:09:10,204
[Anson sighs]

110
00:09:10,204 --> 00:09:12,068
Organized crimes
 has been monitoring

111
00:09:12,068 --> 00:09:15,347
a new undercurrent of
 hostility in the mob of late.

112
00:09:15,347 --> 00:09:17,108
- I thought the families
went legit years ago.

113
00:09:17,108 --> 00:09:18,972
- Well, they have
 and they haven't.

114
00:09:18,972 --> 00:09:20,974
I mean, one thing's for certain,

115
00:09:20,974 --> 00:09:23,804
the mafia certainly has
 assimilated into society.

116
00:09:24,943 --> 00:09:26,220
Hell, you can't
 buy a glass of beer

117
00:09:26,220 --> 00:09:27,532
or a gallon of gas
 without the mafia

118
00:09:27,532 --> 00:09:29,292
getting a kickback
somewhere down the line.

119
00:09:29,292 --> 00:09:30,949
- So, why are they still
 warring with each other then?

120
00:09:30,949 --> 00:09:31,778
- They're not.

121
00:09:33,124 --> 00:09:35,091
Somebody from the outside
 is coming at them.

122
00:09:35,091 --> 00:09:36,023
- Who?

123
00:09:36,023 --> 00:09:36,886
- Well, who do you think?

124
00:09:38,336 --> 00:09:40,407
The guys that picked up
 what the mob left behind.

125
00:09:41,822 --> 00:09:43,652
The next generation
 of immigrants?

126
00:09:44,929 --> 00:09:46,206
The Chinese?

127
00:09:47,517 --> 00:09:50,590
I mean, the Triads are
 all fleeing Hong Kong.

128
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:52,212
I guess they figure it's
easier to come over here

129
00:09:52,212 --> 00:09:54,973
and take on our
criminal justice system.

130
00:09:54,973 --> 00:09:56,423
- Yeah, well, I don't see it.

131
00:09:56,423 --> 00:09:58,011
- Yeah, but these
 are smart guys.

132
00:09:58,011 --> 00:10:00,220
I mean, they kept chipping
 away, chipping away

133
00:10:00,220 --> 00:10:03,430
until they found somebody that
 could open up the back door.

134
00:10:03,430 --> 00:10:06,019
Somebody who will let 'em
 in, make some introductions.

135
00:10:06,019 --> 00:10:07,986
They settled on this
 mid-level hood from Jersey

136
00:10:07,986 --> 00:10:10,126
who just got relocated out West.

137
00:10:10,126 --> 00:10:12,750
Guy got a little too
 ambitious for his own good.

138
00:10:12,750 --> 00:10:13,923
You know, the Triads are wining

139
00:10:13,923 --> 00:10:15,615
and dining the hell out of him.

140
00:10:15,615 --> 00:10:18,410
He's gonna be their entree
 into the power base,

141
00:10:18,410 --> 00:10:20,792
setting him up with his
own little organization.

142
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:24,554
Organized Crimes calls
 him the Toy Godfather.

143
00:10:24,554 --> 00:10:26,626
He's got like his own
 little empire already.

144
00:10:28,006 --> 00:10:29,318
I don't know, maybe
 you've heard of this guy.

145
00:10:29,318 --> 00:10:30,802
Carlo Augustine.

146
00:10:30,802 --> 00:10:33,702
[soft piano music]

147
00:10:44,816 --> 00:10:46,266
Nick, you okay?

148
00:10:50,097 --> 00:10:51,271
You all right, man?

149
00:10:51,271 --> 00:10:52,410
- Yeah, yeah, I'm fine.

150
00:10:53,514 --> 00:10:54,757
I'm fine.

151
00:10:54,757 --> 00:10:57,657
- Anyway, this guy came
up through the ranks.

152
00:10:57,657 --> 00:10:59,797
He has some lineage.

153
00:10:59,797 --> 00:11:01,833
His father was
 Armando Augustine.

154
00:11:03,283 --> 00:11:04,525
I mean, to the mafia families,

155
00:11:04,525 --> 00:11:07,252
this guy was il
 capo di tutti capi.

156
00:11:07,252 --> 00:11:09,047
The godfather.

157
00:11:10,428 --> 00:11:11,947
He was a tough old bastard too.

158
00:11:13,258 --> 00:11:14,743
I think it was back in the '60s

159
00:11:14,743 --> 00:11:16,641
when one of his
 paisans took him out.

160
00:11:18,194 --> 00:11:20,990
The hit wiped out the whole
family except for the two kids.

161
00:11:20,990 --> 00:11:22,336
Two sons.

162
00:11:22,336 --> 00:11:23,683
Carlo was the oldest.

163
00:11:25,132 --> 00:11:27,687
Now the Triads are setting
 him up out here, out West,

164
00:11:27,687 --> 00:11:29,723
down out of Palm Springs.

165
00:11:29,723 --> 00:11:31,242
- What happened
 to the other boy?

166
00:11:31,242 --> 00:11:34,728
- Oh yeah, well, he was just
 a little kid at the time.

167
00:11:34,728 --> 00:11:36,661
Nobody really knows
 what happened to him.

