180
00:12:30,439 --> 00:12:31,371
- [Nick Recording]
 Hi, leave a message

181
00:12:31,371 --> 00:12:33,200
and have yourself a good day.

182
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:34,719
[answering machine beeps]

183
00:12:34,719 --> 00:12:36,583
- [Anson] Nick, it's Anson.

184
00:12:36,583 --> 00:12:39,034
Come on, bud, I
 know you're there.

185
00:12:39,034 --> 00:12:40,760
Pick up or I'm
 sending a squad car.

186
00:12:42,762 --> 00:12:44,556
All right, I'm giving
 you a three-count.

187
00:12:44,556 --> 00:12:46,179
One, two.

188
00:12:48,112 --> 00:12:49,596
- Hi, Mom.

189
00:12:49,596 --> 00:12:51,563
- [Anson] You okay, bub?

190
00:12:51,563 --> 00:12:52,806
- I'm fine.

191
00:12:52,806 --> 00:12:54,635
I guess I just must
 be a little burnt out.

192
00:12:54,635 --> 00:12:55,947
- [Anson] Can't handle
 the pressure, huh?

193
00:12:55,947 --> 00:12:57,328
I always knew you were soft.

194
00:12:58,812 --> 00:13:01,608
My top boy goes AWOL, I'm
 going berserk around here.

195
00:13:01,608 --> 00:13:03,783
Seriously though, I was
 getting a little worried.

196
00:13:03,783 --> 00:13:05,957
- Hey, I'm sorry about
that, Ans, I really am.

197
00:13:05,957 --> 00:13:10,306
- [Anson] Look, you want
 some R & R, you got it, bub.

198
00:13:10,306 --> 00:13:13,137
God knows you put in more
 time than any five of my DAs.

199
00:13:13,137 --> 00:13:15,518
You got enough sick
time and vacation leave

200
00:13:15,518 --> 00:13:16,865
coming to cruise for a while.

201
00:13:16,865 --> 00:13:18,798
- Great, that
 sounds good, thanks.

202
00:13:18,798 --> 00:13:19,937
- [Anson] Anyway.

203
00:13:19,937 --> 00:13:21,904
It's good to know
you're all right, buddy.

204
00:13:21,904 --> 00:13:23,216
- Okay, you take care now.

205
00:13:25,701 --> 00:13:27,323
Something was
 stirring inside me,

206
00:13:27,323 --> 00:13:28,946
it was like pulling me back.

207
00:13:28,946 --> 00:13:30,464
I felt like I was going crazy.

208
00:13:31,603 --> 00:13:33,364
- You saying that
 your strange behavior

209
00:13:33,364 --> 00:13:35,953
was caused by some kind
 of schizophrenia episode?

210
00:13:37,195 --> 00:13:39,370
- You've got to
 understand something.

211
00:13:39,370 --> 00:13:41,372
I'm going along,
 see, living the life.

212
00:13:42,442 --> 00:13:44,237
Doing the job,
 thinking I'm this guy.

213
00:13:44,237 --> 00:13:47,240
And one day I found
 out I'm not me.

214
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:48,448
I'm somebody else.

215
00:13:49,621 --> 00:13:51,071
Somebody born out
 of a nightmare.

216
00:13:52,935 --> 00:13:54,592
- So, your conversation
with Waverley

217
00:13:54,592 --> 00:13:56,352
at the racquetball court,

218
00:13:56,352 --> 00:13:58,665
that's what prompted you
to go to Palm Springs?

219
00:14:00,184 --> 00:14:02,082
- Something was
 eating at me inside.

220
00:14:03,601 --> 00:14:05,914
If Carlo was out there,
then I had to find him.

221
00:14:07,260 --> 00:14:10,159
A buddy of mine at the
 Palm Springs DA office

222
00:14:10,159 --> 00:14:11,126
gave me the name
 of the restaurant

223
00:14:11,126 --> 00:14:13,818
the local wise guys hung out.

224
00:14:13,818 --> 00:14:16,441
I wasn't the only one
 staking out the joint.

225
00:14:16,441 --> 00:14:19,582
[camera clicks]

226
00:14:19,582 --> 00:14:21,584
- What were you
 expecting to find?

227
00:14:23,276 --> 00:14:26,727
[soft piano music]

228
00:14:26,727 --> 00:14:28,108
[camera clicks]

229
