You know anything about
any Triad assassins?

1039
01:05:02,243 --> 01:05:03,071
Yeah.

1040
01:05:04,279 --> 01:05:06,419
I had to do some house
 cleaning for Mr. Wing.

1041
01:05:07,558 --> 01:05:09,526
Now, we've got the
 right people in place.

1042
01:05:10,907 --> 01:05:14,565
You're looking at the new
 West Coast Chinese connection.

1043
01:05:14,565 --> 01:05:16,636
[Wing laughs]

1044
01:05:16,636 --> 01:05:18,431
And you're in it too, Nick.

1045
01:05:18,431 --> 01:05:19,674
Keep it in the family.

1046
01:05:21,020 --> 01:05:23,057
We're gonna do some
 serious business together.

1047
01:05:27,130 --> 01:05:29,477
- Would you excuse us, please?

1048
01:05:29,477 --> 01:05:32,204
I want to talk to
 Nicholas alone.

1049
01:05:33,343 --> 01:05:35,000
- More dirty little
 secrets, Manny?

1050
01:05:35,000 --> 01:05:35,862
- Oh.

1051
01:05:37,830 --> 01:05:41,454
- Ciao, babe.
[lips smacking]

1052
01:05:41,454 --> 01:05:46,183
- The truth is I am an old
 man with very few pleasures.

1053
01:05:49,152 --> 01:05:52,120
Now, that I look
back on my life,

1054
01:05:52,120 --> 01:05:55,952
I am not very proud
 of my accomplishments,

1055
01:05:55,952 --> 01:05:57,781
although I am proud of you.

1056
01:05:59,610 --> 01:06:02,682
But this is not what
 I wanted for you.

1057
01:06:02,682 --> 01:06:05,996
No, this is not at
 all what I wanted.

1058
01:06:07,170 --> 01:06:12,037
For you, a judge,
 maybe a senator.

1059
01:06:13,176 --> 01:06:15,178
Maybe even president
like Jack Kennedy, hmm?

1060
01:06:17,180 --> 01:06:18,975
But that is not to be.

1061
01:06:20,183 --> 01:06:23,082
You are involved with Carlo.

1062
01:06:25,912 --> 01:06:28,363
Fate is playing a cruel game.

1063
01:06:30,193 --> 01:06:31,918
- I've come to accept it, Manny.

1064
01:06:34,128 --> 01:06:36,164
Questa e mia familia.

1065
01:06:39,996 --> 01:06:43,171
- Nicholas, you are
 not of this family!

1066
01:06:44,931 --> 01:06:46,105
- What do you mean?

1067
01:06:46,105 --> 01:06:47,589
- I raised you,
 not these carbones!

1068
01:06:48,901 --> 01:06:50,730
You were not to be part of this!

1069
01:06:51,973 --> 01:06:53,733
- I saw his criminal
 record, Manny.

1070
01:06:55,080 --> 01:06:56,805
How did he get to
 become so powerful?

1071
01:06:56,805 --> 01:06:59,774
- Well, he's connected,
very high up.

1072
01:06:59,774 --> 01:07:02,190
Someone very powerful
 is watching over him.

1073
01:07:02,190 --> 01:07:06,539
And now the Chinese
 want his allegiance.

1074
01:07:06,539 --> 01:07:08,714
But it's you I'm worried about.

1075
01:07:08,714 --> 01:07:12,062
You're dug in, your
life is forever changed.

1076
01:07:12,062 --> 01:07:13,788
You are a gangster.

1077
01:07:19,449 --> 01:07:24,005
I was young once myself
 and full of bright ideas.

1078
01:07:24,005 --> 01:07:28,078
Then I took a couple of
cases I shouldn't have.

1079
01:07:28,078 --> 01:07:30,494
Oh, the money was very good.

1080
01:07:31,840 --> 01:07:34,740
And soon, I was in.

1081
01:07:37,639 --> 01:07:40,366
Look, I can arrange to get
 you out of the country,

1082
01:07:40,366 --> 01:07:42,782
but you have to act at once.

1083
01:07:42,782 --> 01:07:44,163
- I can take care of myself.

1084
01:07:45,923 --> 01:07:46,752
- Can you?

1085
01:07:49,548 --> 01:07:50,687
You really think so.

1086
01:07:55,485 --> 01:07:58,660
Then you are in, and
 I can't help you.

1087
01:08:20,441 --> 01:08:22,063
- [Carlo] What do you want?

1088
01:08:22,063 --> 01:08:22,891
I guessed wrong.

1089
01:08:26,654 --> 01:08:30,140
No, it's family,
it's my problem.

1090
01:08:31,590 --> 01:08:32,936
I'll take care of it.

1091
01:08:37,492 --> 01:08:40,909
[footsteps pattering]

1092
01:08:40,909 --> 01:08:41,738
- [Nick] Carlo.

1093
01:08:41,738 --> 01:08:43,119
- Hey, there he is.

1094
01:08:44,879 --> 01:08:45,811
- What's going on?

1095
01:08:45,811 --> 01:08:47,813
- I gotta get outta here, today.

1096
01:08:47,813 --> 01:08:49,159
- What for?

1097
01:08:49,159 --> 01:08:50,402
- Killing that cop's
 bringing too much heat on us.

1098
01:08:50,402 --> 01:08:51,334
Silvio's bringing
 the car around.

1099
01:08:51,334 --> 01:08:52,749
Come on, Gabrielle, let's go.

1100
01:08:57,616 --> 01:08:58,479
Now!

1101
01:08:58,479 --> 01:09:01,551
[footsteps pattering]

1102
01:09:01,551 --> 01:09:05,658
- It's unseasonably chilly
today, you should dress warmly.

1103
01:09:07,660 --> 01:09:08,903
- I got a sweater.

1104
01:09:08,903 --> 01:09:09,938
- You'll need it.

1105
01:09:17,567 --> 01:09:18,395
Great.

1106
01:09:20,846 --> 01:09:23,573
[tires rumbling]

1107
01:09:34,342 --> 01:09:36,344
[car doors slamming]

1108
01:09:36,344 --> 01:09:37,966
- Yeah, this is all right.

1109
01:09:39,727 --> 01:09:43,351
Hey, Silvio, go get the picnic
 basket out of the trunk.

1110
01:09:56,606 --> 01:09:59,574
I know you're packing,
 Nicky, hand it over.

1111
01:10:02,750 --> 01:10:04,200
Come on, don't play games.

1112
01:10:11,448 --> 01:10:12,277
Come on.

1113
01:10:17,213 --> 01:10:18,559
- Carlo, he's your brother.

1114
01:10:18,559 --> 01:10:19,387
- Shut up.

1115
01:10:22,528 --> 01:10:24,737
I heard you pick up on
 the phone last night.

1116
01:10:28,431 --> 01:10:29,673
- Let's do it.

1117
01:10:29,673 --> 01:10:30,985
- Start walking.

1118
01:10:35,955 --> 01:10:38,924
Come on, you, I want
 you to see this.

1119
01:10:38,924 --> 01:10:40,236
- God, you're hurting me!

1120
01:10:40,236 --> 01:10:42,272
- Good, you cheat on me!

1121
01:10:43,239 --> 01:10:45,033
What, you think I didn't know?

1122
01:10:45,033 --> 01:10:46,000
- Let her go, Carlo.

1123
01:10:47,657 --> 01:10:49,072
- One shot, Nicky.

1124
01:10:50,936 --> 01:10:52,075
You won't even hear it.

1125
01:10:54,111 --> 01:10:56,010
That's how I took Sammy G out.

1126
01:10:56,010 --> 01:10:57,667
I shot him right
 through the ears.

1127
01:10:58,909 --> 01:11:00,117
They had to bury him
 in a closed casket,

1128
01:11:00,117 --> 01:11:01,395
and I laughed at his funeral.

1129
01:11:01,395 --> 01:11:04,052
10 years I waited to
get close to that prick!

1130
01:11:06,020 --> 01:11:07,297
Just like I am to you.

1131
01:11:09,472 --> 01:11:13,269
- Hey, Carlo, you gonna do it?

1132
01:11:13,269 --> 01:11:18,274
Then you go ahead and you do it.

1133
01:11:19,033 --> 01:11:19,999
- That a boy, Nicky.

1134
01:11:21,794 --> 01:11:22,623
Don't beg.

1135
01:11:23,865 --> 01:11:26,627
Sammy G begged and
 cried like a baby.

1136
01:11:28,076 --> 01:11:31,321
And you know what he told me
 before I blew his brains out?

1137
01:11:32,736 --> 01:11:37,534
He said, "Killing your
 Papa was just a contract.

1138
01:11:38,294 --> 01:11:40,813
"You know, business."

1139
01:11:42,539 --> 01:11:44,472
- Is this business too, Carlo?

1140
01:11:45,439 --> 01:11:49,235
- No, this is self-preservation.

1141
01:11:50,478 --> 01:11:51,859
[suspenseful music]

1142
01:11:51,859 --> 01:11:56,001
[gunshot blasting]
 [Gabrielle screaming]

1143
01:11:56,001 --> 01:11:59,832
[Gabrielle whimpering]

1144
01:11:59,832 --> 01:12:01,558
I could kill you,
 don't you know that?

1145
01:12:01,558 --> 01:12:03,146
- What the hell
 is going on here?

1146
01:12:03,146 --> 01:12:05,217
- I'm saving your
 ass like I always do!

1147
01:12:06,563 --> 01:12:08,703
Silvio turned, cut his
 own deal with Wing.

1148
01:12:08,703 --> 01:12:10,395
He would have
 whacked you himself.

1149
01:12:11,361 --> 01:12:12,845
I had to get up close.

1150
01:12:12,845 --> 01:12:13,674
Hit men.

1151
01:12:15,745 --> 01:12:17,298
They could smell fear.

1152
01:12:18,506 --> 01:12:19,921
- You used me as a
 diversion, didn't you?

1153
01:12:19,921 --> 01:12:21,095
- Family business, Nicky.

1154
01:12:21,095 --> 01:12:22,752
You're family, I
never forget it.

1155
01:12:24,892 --> 01:12:26,963
Now, I got one more
 thing to do for Papa.

1156
01:12:29,759 --> 01:12:31,174
- Papa's been dead 20 years.

1157
01:12:33,487 --> 01:12:34,936
When are you gonna let it go?

1158
01:12:39,769 --> 01:12:43,220
- You want to know
 the truth, Nicky?

1159
01:12:43,220 --> 01:12:45,464
I died in that room that day.

1160
01:12:47,742 --> 01:12:50,400
My whole life's been
 spent avenging Papa.

1161
01:12:53,369 --> 01:12:54,300
I'm almost done.

1162
01:12:57,234 --> 01:12:59,202
But you got a life ahead of you.

1163
01:13:00,928 --> 01:13:03,033
Now get outta here and
 take here with you.

1164
01:13:04,966 --> 01:13:06,623
- Carlo, you come back with me,

1165
01:13:06,623 --> 01:13:09,764
I'll put you in the
 witness protection program.

1166
01:13:09,764 --> 01:13:10,972
I can help you.

1167
01:13:10,972 --> 01:13:12,905
- You're a good
 kid, you know that?

1168
01:13:16,322 --> 01:13:19,153
Here, I want you to
 have Papa's ring.

1169
01:13:22,915 --> 01:13:24,400
- I can help the both of you.

1170
01:13:25,504 --> 01:13:27,506
- I can't, it's destiny.

1171
01:13:31,165 --> 01:13:35,341
By the time you get back
 to LA, it'll all be over.

1172
01:13:41,037 --> 01:13:44,799
- Carlo, you can't
leave me here like this.

1173
01:13:44,799 --> 01:13:46,249
- Hey, Gabrielle, you're the
 eighth wonder of the world,

1174
01:13:46,249 --> 01:13:50,667
you know that, hm?
 [lips smacking]

1175
01:13:50,667 --> 01:13:52,289
But you gotta go where your
 bread's buttered right?

1176
01:13:52,289 --> 01:13:54,153
Now, your bread's
 buttered with squirt.

1177
01:13:54,153 --> 01:13:55,810
- I don't want this.

1178
01:13:56,846 --> 01:13:58,779
- Like Manny always says,

1179
01:14:00,090 --> 01:14:02,368
you lie down with dogs,
you get up with fleas.

1180
01:14:03,853 --> 01:14:06,856
[suspenseful music]

1181
01:14:12,827 --> 01:14:14,311
- Carlo.
 - I gotta go.

1182
01:14:15,174 --> 01:14:16,003
Family.

1183
01:14:17,142 --> 01:14:20,145
[suspenseful music]

1184
01:14:29,499 --> 01:14:32,122
[gun clicking]

1185
01:14:35,160 --> 01:14:38,163
[gunshots blasting]

1186
01:14:42,374 --> 01:14:45,135
[hood clanging]

1187
01:14:45,135 --> 01:14:48,138
[suspenseful music]

1188
01:14:51,970 --> 01:14:53,040
- Carlo!

1189
01:14:53,040 --> 01:14:55,629
[car crashing]

1190
01:14:57,596 --> 01:15:01,220
[door slamming]
 [gunshot blasting]

1191
01:15:01,220 --> 01:15:03,464
[bullet squelching]

1192
01:15:03,464 --> 01:15:06,778
[gun clicking]

1193
01:15:06,778 --> 01:15:09,366
[gentle music]

1194
01:15:41,295 --> 01:15:44,298
[suspenseful music]

1195
01:15:47,543 --> 01:15:52,548
[gun clicking]
 [Nick panting]

1196
01:15:53,790 --> 01:15:56,172
[gun thudding]

1197
01:15:56,172 --> 01:15:59,175
[suspenseful music]

1198
01:16:10,324 --> 01:16:13,051
[shoes thudding]

1199
01:16:17,918 --> 01:16:21,369
[Wing grunting]

1200
01:16:21,369 --> 01:16:26,374
[fists smashing]
[men grunting]

1201
01:16:27,686 --> 01:16:31,103
[knees smashing]
[men grunting]

1202
01:16:31,103 --> 01:16:34,106
[suspenseful music]

1203
01:16:40,078 --> 01:16:41,079
[Nick grunting]
[pipe whacking]

1204
01:16:41,079 --> 01:16:43,771
[knife thudding]
[body thudding]

1205
01:16:43,771 --> 01:16:46,774
[suspenseful music]

1206
01:16:54,195 --> 01:16:56,922
[knife thudding]

1207
01:16:59,097 --> 01:17:02,410
[suspenseful music]

1208
01:17:02,410 --> 01:17:07,415
[motor humming]
 [tires screeching]

1209
01:17:08,140 --> 01:17:11,005
[suspenseful music]

1210
01:17:23,259 --> 01:17:28,264
[car crashing]
 [explosion blasting]

1211
01:17:35,616 --> 01:17:38,067
[lighter clicking]

1212
01:17:38,067 --> 01:17:40,656
- You know, I gotta confide
 something in you, Nick.

1213
01:17:43,313 --> 01:17:46,144
You're like a tar
 baby of misery.

1214
01:17:46,144 --> 01:17:48,042
Anyone who touches you dies.

1215
01:17:49,285 --> 01:17:50,113
By the way.

1216
01:17:52,737 --> 01:17:54,083
Where's your fucking badge?

1217
01:17:59,191 --> 01:18:00,537
- I left it in my apartment.

1218
01:18:02,643 --> 01:18:05,301
You see, I didn't know who
 the good guys were anymore.

1219
01:18:09,477 --> 01:18:13,274
- What about Wing, why
 didn't you kill him?

1220
01:18:13,274 --> 01:18:16,484
He tried to kill you,
he killed your brother.

1221
01:18:16,484 --> 01:18:17,693
Why didn't you kill him?

1222
01:18:21,075 --> 01:18:23,526
- The apple doesn't
fall far from the tree.

1223
01:18:26,356 --> 01:18:27,737
I didn't have it in me then,

1224
01:18:30,706 --> 01:18:32,431
and I don't know
 now, Mr. Winslow.

1225
01:18:40,163 --> 01:18:41,682
- [Winslow] You're free to go.

1226
01:18:46,238 --> 01:18:47,446
- Nicholas!

1227
01:18:47,446 --> 01:18:49,241
- Surprised to see me, Manny?

1228
01:18:49,241 --> 01:18:52,486
- Oh, Nicholas, you could give
 an old man a heart attack.

1229
01:18:52,486 --> 01:18:55,316
- Yeah, if you had a heart.

1230
01:18:57,008 --> 01:18:58,388
- I since hostility.

1231
01:18:58,388 --> 01:18:59,907
- Hostility?

1232
01:18:59,907 --> 01:19:00,701
No.

1233
01:19:01,667 --> 01:19:02,910
I would say that I'm impressed,

1234
01:19:02,910 --> 01:19:03,877
but then I've always
been impressed with you,

1235
01:19:03,877 --> 01:19:05,326
haven't I, Manny?

1236
01:19:05,326 --> 01:19:07,018
- Impressed, that's good?

1237
01:19:07,018 --> 01:19:07,846
- That's good.

1238
01:19:09,261 --> 01:19:10,538
Just like you, Manny.

1239
01:19:14,163 --> 01:19:16,752
- Sit, sit, sit, we'll talk.

1240
01:19:16,752 --> 01:19:19,755
[chair creaking]

1241
01:19:19,755 --> 01:19:22,033
- It took me awhile
 to piece it together.

1242
01:19:23,172 --> 01:19:25,277
It was a bunch of
 little things, really.

1243
01:19:25,277 --> 01:19:29,109
Then I saw the report
 the FBI had on you.

1244
01:19:29,109 --> 01:19:30,558
- The FBI?

1245
01:19:30,558 --> 01:19:32,008
- Yeah.

1246
01:19:32,008 --> 01:19:33,976
They've been watching you
 now for over 20 years.

1247
01:19:33,976 --> 01:19:36,668
- [laughs] That's the
 trouble with this business.

1248
01:19:36,668 --> 01:19:38,946
Someone is always watching you.

1249
01:19:40,120 --> 01:19:42,087
- You covered your
 ass pretty well,

1250
01:19:42,087 --> 01:19:44,296
but there was one small
fact you overlooked.

1251
01:19:47,023 --> 01:19:49,405
- Fact, what fact?

1252
01:19:49,405 --> 01:19:51,752
- You were my
 father's consigliere.

1253
01:19:51,752 --> 01:19:53,512
- Yeah, that's
 true, you knew that.

1254
01:19:53,512 --> 01:19:56,308
- And then you went
 to work for Sammy G.

1255
01:19:56,308 --> 01:19:58,655
- [laughs] Sammy G.

1256
01:20:00,174 --> 01:20:02,004
When he took over your
 father's concerns,

1257
01:20:02,004 --> 01:20:03,074
he took me with him.

1258
01:20:04,454 --> 01:20:05,662
In this business,

1259
01:20:05,662 --> 01:20:07,733
you always go where
your bread is buttered.

1260
01:20:07,733 --> 01:20:09,390
- You were heavily connected.

1261
01:20:10,633 --> 01:20:13,084
You were watching over Carlo.

1262
01:20:13,084 --> 01:20:15,120
You weren't working for him.

1263
01:20:15,120 --> 01:20:17,467
He was working for you,
only he didn't know it.

1264
01:20:18,779 --> 01:20:21,747
- In my own way, I was
watching over both of you boys.

1265
01:20:21,747 --> 01:20:25,027
- No, and Carlo was on to you.

1266
01:20:25,027 --> 01:20:26,683
- On to me?

1267
01:20:26,683 --> 01:20:28,824
Why should Carlo be on to me?

1268
01:20:28,824 --> 01:20:29,997
For what?

1269
01:20:29,997 --> 01:20:33,587
- I remember that day,
 that terrible day.

1270
01:20:35,140 --> 01:20:37,246
We were in the living
 room when they came.

1271
01:20:38,212 --> 01:20:39,800
The noise was like thunder.

1272
01:20:39,800 --> 01:20:44,598
[gunshots blasting]
 [thunder cracking]

1273
01:20:44,598 --> 01:20:47,566
[suspenseful music]

1274
01:21:19,322 --> 01:21:20,496
He brought me to you.

1275
01:21:22,567 --> 01:21:23,775
To you, Manny.

1276
01:21:23,775 --> 01:21:25,535
You were waiting
 outside in the car.

1277
01:21:27,227 --> 01:21:29,056
You knew what was going on.

1278
01:21:29,056 --> 01:21:33,612
- Nicholas, you hurt me
with these accusations.

1279
01:21:33,612 --> 01:21:34,682
- Come on, Manny.

1280
01:21:36,236 --> 01:21:38,583
Carlo didn't fake his
 death to see what I'd do.

1281
01:21:39,756 --> 01:21:41,172
He wanted to see
 what you would do.

1282
01:21:44,554 --> 01:21:45,555
And what did you do?

1283
01:21:47,212 --> 01:21:49,318
You put a contract out on me.

1284
01:21:49,318 --> 01:21:50,906
- Oh, you, no.

1285
01:21:50,906 --> 01:21:53,149
I never sent the
 assassins after you.

1286
01:21:53,149 --> 01:21:55,945
That was Silvio's doing, alone.

1287
01:21:57,222 --> 01:22:00,708
Later I learned that
 Wing didn't trust you.

1288
01:22:00,708 --> 01:22:02,400
And I was outraged.

1289
01:22:02,400 --> 01:22:04,298
- I'm not talking
 about the assassins.

1290
01:22:05,472 --> 01:22:06,818
It was the state trooper.

1291
01:22:09,303 --> 01:22:10,442
You don't buy the state police

1292
01:22:10,442 --> 01:22:11,892
unless you got a lotta juice.

1293
01:22:12,962 --> 01:22:14,722
And you got a
 lotta juice, Manny.

1294
01:22:15,723 --> 01:22:16,932
And then when I came back,

1295
01:22:16,932 --> 01:22:18,519
you knew he had to
 get rid of both of us.

1296
01:22:18,519 --> 01:22:19,313
- No.

1297
01:22:20,556 --> 01:22:21,833
Nicholas, I love you.

1298
01:22:21,833 --> 01:22:23,317
Don't be ridiculous.

1299
01:22:23,317 --> 01:22:27,321
- The day Carlo died, he
 knew I was carrying a gun.

1300
01:22:28,633 --> 01:22:29,530
You told him.

1301
01:22:30,669 --> 01:22:33,741
You set it up so we'd
 both shoot it out.

1302
01:22:40,231 --> 01:22:43,303
[fist slams]
 [Manny sighs]

1303
01:22:43,303 --> 01:22:47,238
- So many years, the guilt.

1304
01:22:48,273 --> 01:22:50,655
I am not a perfect person.

1305
01:22:54,107 --> 01:22:55,625
This is the hard part.

1306
01:22:59,871 --> 01:23:02,839
Armand Augustine
 is not your father.

1307
01:23:03,806 --> 01:23:07,016
[crickets chirping]

1308
01:23:07,016 --> 01:23:08,466
You are my son.

1309
01:23:16,025 --> 01:23:17,509
Nicolas, I love you.

1310
01:23:21,479 --> 01:23:24,516
Armand Augustine
 was a brutal man.

1311
01:23:24,516 --> 01:23:25,448
And he had no vision.

1312
01:23:25,448 --> 01:23:26,898
I made him great!

1313
01:23:28,313 --> 01:23:31,937
But all he saw was a fixer,
 someone to do legal work.

1314
01:23:33,836 --> 01:23:36,977
Then your mother
 and I fell in love.

1315
01:23:36,977 --> 01:23:40,601
It was not supposed to happen
 that way, but things happen.

1316
01:23:42,224 --> 01:23:43,742
She couldn't leave her husband.

1317
01:23:43,742 --> 01:23:45,330
He would have killed us both.

1318
01:23:47,125 --> 01:23:49,714
Then he found out about us.

1319
01:23:49,714 --> 01:23:50,542
And then you.

1320
01:23:52,786 --> 01:23:57,791
He gave Sammy G the hit on
 me and I turned the tables.

1321
01:24:00,690 --> 01:24:05,695
Sammy was no Armand, but
I made him something.

1322
01:24:06,420 --> 01:24:08,698
Then Carlo killed him.

1323
01:24:08,698 --> 01:24:12,495
Carlo could have
 been even greater,

1324
01:24:12,495 --> 01:24:14,670
but all he ever
 wanted was revenge.

1325
01:24:15,843 --> 01:24:18,191
All that anger he
 walked around with.

1326
01:24:20,365 --> 01:24:23,437
And now there's you.

1327
01:24:23,437 --> 01:24:25,681
- And now you have to get
 rid of me, don't you, Manny?

1328
01:24:25,681 --> 01:24:28,201
- May God strike me dead.

1329
01:24:28,201 --> 01:24:30,858
- Yeah, well you should have
 when you had the chance.

1330
01:24:32,688 --> 01:24:34,483
The Feds picked me
 up the other day.

1331
01:24:36,519 --> 01:24:38,832
They told me that
 the hit's out on you.

1332
01:24:40,075 --> 01:24:42,111
The Triads have you
 marked for death.

1333
01:24:44,217 --> 01:24:45,632
You're caught in the middle.

1334
01:24:46,840 --> 01:24:48,566
- Goddamn!

1335
01:24:48,566 --> 01:24:51,086
Even in death, Carlo
 has me by the balls!

1336
01:24:54,330 --> 01:24:57,575
His hotheaded plan
 started all of this.

1337
01:24:58,507 --> 01:25:01,441
[crickets chirping]

1338
01:25:08,275 --> 01:25:10,105
Can you help me out of this?

1339
01:25:12,797 --> 01:25:13,625
- No.

1340
01:25:16,663 --> 01:25:18,423
- You reap what you sow.

1341
01:25:22,324 --> 01:25:24,947
Well, at least try
 to save yourself, eh.

1342
01:25:26,811 --> 01:25:28,295
- Don't worry about me, Manny.

1343
01:25:29,434 --> 01:25:30,401
I'll be okay.

1344
01:25:32,472 --> 01:25:37,373
- You know, ironically,
I'm very proud of you.

1345
01:25:46,555 --> 01:25:51,560
Goodbye, my son.

1346
01:25:55,150 --> 01:25:56,565
- Goodbye, Manny.

1347
01:26:03,848 --> 01:26:06,609
[birds chirping]

1348
01:26:08,784 --> 01:26:10,165
[Manny sighs]

1349
01:26:10,165 --> 01:26:12,857
[glasses clink]

1350
01:26:15,584 --> 01:26:18,587
[suspenseful music]

1351
01:26:35,017 --> 01:26:36,260
[knife whooshing]

1352
01:26:36,260 --> 01:26:39,642
[knife squelching]
 [glass shattering]

1353
01:26:39,642 --> 01:26:42,542
[liquor splashing]

1354
01:26:47,788 --> 01:26:50,722
[soft piano music]

1355
01:26:54,001 --> 01:26:56,763
[tires rumbling]

1356
01:26:59,524 --> 01:27:02,355
[soft piano music]

1357
01:27:19,303 --> 01:27:21,995
[door thudding]

1358
01:27:34,007 --> 01:27:37,010
- [Nick Voiceover] Why was I
 under investigation, Anson?

1359
01:27:37,010 --> 01:27:39,702
- [Anson] What makes
 you think that?

1360
01:27:39,702 --> 01:27:41,463
You know, they happened
to find your name

1361
01:27:41,463 --> 01:27:43,396
buried inside another
 investigation?

1362
01:27:45,501 --> 01:27:46,606
You had us worried.

1363
01:27:47,607 --> 01:27:50,265
And were trying to find out...

1364
01:27:50,265 --> 01:27:52,405
- [Nick Voiceover] Which side
 I was buttering my bread.

1365
01:27:53,751 --> 01:27:56,995
- [Anson] No, son
 of the godfather.

1366
01:27:57,893 --> 01:27:59,170
I mean, this does not look good

1367
01:27:59,170 --> 01:28:00,861
on the resume of a
 district attorney.

1368
01:28:04,071 --> 01:28:05,832
They found Kohen's
 body on Tuesday.

1369
01:28:07,592 --> 01:28:09,180
He'd been dead about 30 hours.

1370
01:28:10,768 --> 01:28:13,046
Chinese didn't waste any time.

1371
01:28:13,046 --> 01:28:15,428
[ring thuds]

1372
01:28:22,676 --> 01:28:24,195
So, what are you gonna do, bub?

1373
01:28:25,334 --> 01:28:26,784
- [Nick Voiceover]
 Get on with my life.

1374
01:28:28,579 --> 01:28:29,925
- [Anson] Where will you go?

1375
01:28:31,098 --> 01:28:31,892
- [Nick Voiceover] I was
thinking about working

1376
01:28:31,892 --> 01:28:33,100
for organized crimes.

1377
01:28:34,792 --> 01:28:36,241
- [Anson] Why
 should they take ya?

1378
01:28:37,691 --> 01:28:38,692
- [Nick Voiceover]
Because I know something

1379
01:28:38,692 --> 01:28:39,900
about the criminal mind.

1380
01:28:54,501 --> 01:28:55,744
Now, when I look in the mirror,

1381
01:28:55,744 --> 01:28:57,953
I don't see myself
 like I used to.

1382
01:28:59,092 --> 01:29:02,440
I see Carlo and
 Manny and Gabrielle.

1383
01:29:03,993 --> 01:29:06,168
But at least now I
 know where I came from

1384
01:29:06,168 --> 01:29:07,169
and where I'm going.

1385
01:29:08,998 --> 01:29:09,896
And who I am.

1386
01:29:11,242 --> 01:29:12,899
There's always gonna be
a part of me that will

1387
01:29:12,899 --> 01:29:17,593
ask the question, if Carlo
 and I had changed places,

1388
01:29:17,593 --> 01:29:19,112
how would I have turned out?

1389
01:29:20,527 --> 01:29:22,115
[engine revving]

1390
01:29:22,115 --> 01:29:23,806
Cain and Abel,
 they were brothers.

1391
01:29:25,290 --> 01:29:26,637
One became a killer.

1392
01:29:28,880 --> 01:29:31,366
It could have gone either way.

1393
01:29:34,886 --> 01:29:37,820
[soft piano music]

1394
01:30:04,364 --> 01:30:07,367
[tense piano music]

1395
01:31:00,869 --> 01:31:03,768
[soft piano music]

1396
01:31:38,872 --> 01:31:41,875
[tense piano music]

